a contract with you.

14:38.178 --> 14:40.478
There-there are rules
to business, my friend.

14:40.480 --> 14:41.880
Rules.

14:41.882 --> 14:43.815
Now, look,
I-I don't want

14:43.817 --> 14:47.385
to scare you, but if you don't
give us back our company,

14:47.387 --> 14:49.754
you'll be getting a letter.

14:51.557 --> 14:54.392
<i>Capisce?</i>

14:54.394 --> 14:57.395
I say <i>"capisce"</i> to people.
Nobody says <i>"capisce"</i> to me.

14:57.397 --> 14:58.997
<i>Capisce?</i>

14:58.999 --> 15:02.400
No, I don't <i>capisce! Capisce?!</i>

15:02.402 --> 15:05.770
Did you just <i>double-capisce</i> me,
you son of a bitch?!

15:07.206 --> 15:10.975
It's time for you
to leave, Johnny.

15:13.012 --> 15:15.179
If that's the way you feel.

15:15.181 --> 15:18.249
I appreciate your honesty.

15:22.221 --> 15:24.055
Hey, you know what?

15:24.057 --> 15:26.024
Let's go for a ride.

15:26.026 --> 15:27.025
A ride?

15:27.027 --> 15:29.093
Warner, run!

15:36.035 --> 15:38.069
I can't believe they
took my best friend.

15:38.071 --> 15:39.537
I know.

15:39.539 --> 15:42.073
I can't believe
you let them.

15:42.075 --> 15:44.409
Let them? What was
I supposed to do?

15:44.411 --> 15:45.877
They're bigger than me.

15:45.879 --> 15:47.211
Everybody's bigger than you.

15:47.213 --> 15:49.247
Really? Now?

15:49.249 --> 15:52.717
Okay, I got Johnny's
cell phone number.

15:52.719 --> 15:55.887
I'm sure we can
reason with him.

15:55.889 --> 15:57.055
JOHNNY (recorded):
This is Johnny.

15:57.057 --> 15:58.122
If you're calling
to reason with me,

15:58.124 --> 16:00.191
forget about it.

16:01.727 --> 16:04.562
Well, I don't care if we have
to drive down every street

16:04.564 --> 16:07.065
in this city,
we're gonna go find him.

16:07.067 --> 16:09.500
Eli, I can tell you
where they're going.

16:14.740 --> 16:17.041
We really bonded
at that lap dance.

16:18.243 --> 16:22.113
Johnny has a warehouse
at the end of Anchor Avenue.

16:22.115 --> 16:23.081
I can take you there.

16:23.083 --> 16:25.483
No, White Wine,
you stay here.

16:25.485 --> 16:27.318
And try to...

16:27.320 --> 16:30.555
try to get those last two
ping-pong balls out, okay?

16:40.599 --> 16:42.934
Hey, did-did I ever
tell you that

16:42.936 --> 16:46.270
in high school, I was voted Most
Likely to Gladly Change My Name

16:46.272 --> 16:48.573
and-and Move to Another Country?

16:52.778 --> 16:55.646
This <i>fugacci</i> computer
says we're in the ocean.

16:55.648 --> 16:57.982
Oh, yeah, you just have
to, uh, uh, download

16:57.984 --> 17:00.118
the-the latest operating system
and, uh...

17:00.120 --> 17:02.620
and-and upgrade the interface.

17:02.622 --> 17:05.857
Who are you,
Bill Nye the Science <i>Squalootz?</i>

17:05.859 --> 17:09.160
(laughs):
That's funny.

17:09.162 --> 17:11.863
Do you mind if I...
do you mind if I try to fix it?

17:11.865 --> 17:13.531
Yeah, okay.

17:13.533 --> 17:14.966
Yeah, let me just, uh...

17:14.968 --> 17:17.468
(beeping)

17:17.470 --> 17:19.637
A second to reboot.
Yeah, there it is.

17:19.639 --> 17:22.206
Hey, you're pretty good
at this computer crap.
Yeah.

17:22.208 --> 17:24.175
You ever think about starting
your own business?

17:24.177 --> 17:28.846
Well, I did, but the, uh...
the Mafia took it over.

17:28.848 --> 17:31.215
Oh, right, right.
Sorry.

17:31.217 --> 17:34.552
Sometimes you forget the reason
you're about to whack somebody.

17:34.554 --> 17:35.987
Tell me about it.

17:35.989 --> 17:38.990
I've had this string tied
around my finger for two months.

17:38.992 --> 17:43.895
Somebody's walking around
unstrangled-- I don't know.

17:46.832 --> 17:49.567
Eli, what exactly is your plan
when we get there?

17:49.569 --> 17:51.402
I don't know. Do you
think we can lure them

17:51.404 --> 17:53.004
into a house of mirrors?

17:53.006 --> 17:53.905
(groans)

17:53.907 --> 17:57.575
Why do I have to come?
He's not my son.

17:58.677 --> 18:00.912
Crawford, Johnny's your friend.
Mm-hmm.

18:00.914 --> 18:03.181
I mean, you don't think he'd
actually hurt Warner, right?

18:03.183 --> 18:05.583
I don't know.
You know, Johnny talks big,

18:05.585 --> 18:08.086
but the worst thing
I've ever seen him do

18:08.088 --> 18:09.587
is strangle a racehorse.

18:13.358 --> 18:15.760
Nobody insults Johnny Johnny
DeSalvo DeSalvo

18:15.762 --> 18:17.261
and lives to talk about it.

18:17.263 --> 18:18.529
MEN:
Yeah!

18:18.531 --> 18:21.365
Any last words before you sleep
with the fishes?

18:21.367 --> 18:25.103
ELI: Yeah. Let
our friend go.

18:28.540 --> 18:32.877
What are you <i>gambrozzis </i>
<i>doing here?</i>

18:32.879 --> 18:36.614
Wait, uh, is
<i>"gambrozzis"</i> a bad thing?

18:36.616 --> 18:39.617
It's a neutral term.

18:39.619 --> 18:41.619
Okay. Good.

18:41.621 --> 18:42.887
Well, we came
for Warner!

18:42.889 --> 18:43.955
Yeah!

18:45.424 --> 18:47.391
Hey, guys.

18:47.393 --> 18:49.894
What are you doing here?
Warner! (exhales)

18:49.896 --> 18:51.796
We thought
they were gonna whack you.

18:51.798 --> 18:53.264
JOHNNY:
Yeah, yeah,

18:53.266 --> 18:55.233
we were, but then, uh,
chipmunk-head here said

18:55.235 --> 18:59.904
he could hook up my intranet
with five-point-oh!

18:59.906 --> 19:02.440
Yeah, these guys were
in the Stone Ages.

19:02.442 --> 19:05.643
Th-This guy here thought Google
was a type of bird.

19:05.645 --> 19:07.078
(laughs)

19:07.080 --> 19:10.081
I-It's true, I did.
I don't know.

19:10.083 --> 19:12.750
Wait, if-if you aren't mad
at Warner,

19:12.752 --> 19:14.318
then who were you threatening?

19:15.754 --> 19:17.889
Please help me!

19:20.092 --> 19:23.794
Warner hooked up this, uh,
new program called Skippy.

19:23.796 --> 19:25.229
Skype.

19:30.936 --> 19:32.503
Makes my life so much easier.

19:32.505 --> 19:36.841
Now I can sit around whacking
in my pajamas all day.

19:38.477 --> 19:42.113
I got to get a computer.

19:42.115 --> 19:45.950
Wait, Mr. DeSalvo, it-it sounds
like Warner did you a favor.

19:45.952 --> 19:48.786
Doesn't that mean
you owe him one?

19:48.788 --> 19:52.023
I suppose it does,
my little lotus blossom.

19:55.961 --> 19:58.963
Warner, you can have
your company back.

19:58.965 --> 20:01.032
(chuckles)

20:02.167 --> 20:05.169
Johnny...

20:05.171 --> 20:07.805
you know,
beneath all that bluster,

20:07.807 --> 20:09.173
you got a giant heart.

20:09.175 --> 20:11.475
You're a good man,

20:11.477 --> 20:13.744
and I'm proud
to call you friend.

20:14.713 --> 20:16.781
Come here.
(chuckles)

20:18.483 --> 20:20.218
Isn't anybody gonna do anything?

20:20.220 --> 20:21.552
Hey!

20:21.554 --> 20:23.654
You bet on the Bucks
and you lost, you scumbag.

20:23.656 --> 20:24.989
So just sit still,

20:24.991 --> 20:27.124
and somebody will be there
to whack you shortly.

20:35.167 --> 20:36.834
(Johnny's voice):
Hey, you <i>gambrozzis,</i>

20:36.836 --> 20:38.669
I'm Meatball,
the talking meatball,

20:38.671 --> 20:40.171
and I'm in a video game.

20:40.173 --> 20:43.241
It's funny, right?

20:44.176 --> 20:46.010
It is kind of funny.

20:46.012 --> 20:48.246
I can't believe this tested
higher than any character

20:48.248 --> 20:50.314
we've ever created.

20:53.018 --> 20:57.021
I'll be your consigliere on your
journey from bag boy to don.

20:57.023 --> 20:59.857
So grab your whatchamacallit,
uh, controller?

20:59.859 --> 21:01.692
My sister's kid could tell you.

21:01.694 --> 21:04.362
All day long
with these video game machines.

21:04.364 --> 21:06.030
He's got diabetes.

21:06.032 --> 21:09.100
The good kind, thank God.

21:10.702 --> 21:13.704
And then it basically goes on
like that for the next 40 hours.

21:13.706 --> 21:15.206
Wow.

21:15.208 --> 21:17.375
Hey. Where'd you get
that fur coat?

21:17.377 --> 21:18.442
Mind your business.

21:20.279 --> 21:22.713
Our place just looks
so boring now.

21:22.715 --> 21:24.081
What happened
to all the bada-bling?

21:24.083 --> 21:25.082
Yeah, I got rid of it.

21:25.084 --> 21:26.083
All of it?

21:26.085 --> 21:28.252
Every last piece.

21:28.254 --> 21:31.689
(rock music playing)

21:39.464 --> 21:41.532
(music ends)

21:44.736 --> 21:47.071
My turn!
(music resumes)

